-- Wells Fargo Hires JPMorgan Energy Investment Banker Fornell
-- B y   Z a c h a r y   R .   M i d e r
-- 2012-02-27T14:56:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-27/wells-fargo-hires-jpmorgan-energy-investment-banker-fornell.html
Wells Fargo & Co. (WFC) , the largest U.S.
bank by market value, hired Eric Fornell from  JPMorgan Chase &
Co. (JPM)  to advise energy and power clients in the investment bank.  Fornell, 56, joins as a vice chairman and will focus on
power and pipeline companies, San Francisco-based Wells Fargo
said today in a statement. He was most recently a vice chairman
at JPMorgan, where he worked since 1999.  Prior to JPMorgan, Fornell worked at Goldman Sachs Group
Inc. and at CMS Enterprises Co., Wells Fargo said.  Fornell “brings more than 30 years of well-rounded
experience in banking, M&A and equities,” Rob Engel, a co-head
of investment banking at Wells Fargo, said in the statement.
Fornell is based in  New York  and will report to Engel and the
other co-head, Jonathan Weiss.  To contact the reporter on this story:
